==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# {{AU}} A type of [[melon]], ''[[w:Cucumis melo reticulatus|Cucumis melo reticulatus]]'', with sweet orange flesh and a rough skin resembling netting.  Also known as [[cantaloupe]].

===Usage notes===
In Australia, this fruit (''C. m. reticulatus'') is known as rockmelon in northern states (eg. [[w:Queensland|Queensland]]) and [[cantaloupe]] in southern states (eg. [[w:Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]).